Lisa Frank stuff, I gotta have it, what more can I say, pretty soon my friends Ashley

00:00:27.630 --> 00:00:32.630
and Lindsay are going to Lisa Franks, crazy too, so now we always get together and

00:00:32.630 --> 00:00:37.630
have a dreamy of Seapover, the most outrageous party, and we're in the one and only club, Lisa Franks.

00:00:37.630 --> 00:00:41.630
Now, life's a total blast, Lisa Franks, you gotta have it.

00:00:43.630 --> 00:00:46.630
Team Tiger is brought to you by Kellogg's Frosted Plate.

00:00:46.630 --> 00:00:51.630
We're on the American River at that 15-year-old Kyle Maranella, champion kayaker.

00:00:51.630 --> 00:00:52.630
Where's reverse?

00:00:52.630 --> 00:00:53.630
Here we go.

00:00:53.630 --> 00:00:58.550
How's her and his stripes? So how about you?

00:00:58.550 --> 00:01:00.550
Take practice and good eating.

00:01:01.550 --> 00:01:05.550
Like a complete breakfast with a sweet crunch across the plate cereal.

00:01:05.550 --> 00:01:06.550
There we go.

00:01:07.550 --> 00:01:09.550
You can join the team and bring out the Tiger.

00:01:09.550 --> 00:01:10.550
Yeah!

00:01:10.550 --> 00:01:41.140
Like you stumble, stumble, surprise, eat tumble.

00:01:41.140 --> 00:01:42.140
Baby, stumble, surprise.

00:01:43.140 --> 00:01:44.140
There she is.

00:01:44.140 --> 00:01:45.140
My shell's cracking.

00:01:46.140 --> 00:01:47.140
She's beautiful.

00:01:48.140 --> 00:01:49.140
Here we go.

00:01:52.140 --> 00:02:07.290
Frank.

00:02:10.290 --> 00:02:11.290
Is it loud?

00:02:11.290 --> 00:02:12.290
Yeah.

00:02:12.290 --> 00:02:32.780
Love hurts.

00:02:48.380 --> 00:02:51.380
I was just an average kid until an accident changed my life.

00:02:52.380 --> 00:02:55.380
And since then, nothing's been the same.

00:02:56.380 --> 00:03:20.750
My best friend Ray thinks it's cool.

00:03:23.540 --> 00:03:25.540
My sister Annie thinks it's a science project.

00:03:26.540 --> 00:03:28.540
I can't let anyone else know.

00:03:28.540 --> 00:03:30.540
Not even my parents.

00:03:30.540 --> 00:03:37.360
I know the chemical plant was to find me and turn me into some experiment.

00:03:37.360 --> 00:03:38.360
But you know something?

00:03:38.360 --> 00:03:40.360
I guess I'm not so average anymore.

00:03:40.360 --> 00:03:48.370
Alex, what are you still doing?

00:03:48.370 --> 00:03:49.370
I thought you were one of the movies.

00:03:49.370 --> 00:03:51.370
I am, but Annie's late.

00:03:51.370 --> 00:03:59.160
We have to leave like right now.

00:03:59.160 --> 00:04:01.160
Or I'll just wait until the next showing.

00:04:01.160 --> 00:04:02.160
I can't go to the movies.

00:04:02.160 --> 00:04:05.160
I have so much work to do and then I'm going to Bryce's for dinner.

00:04:05.160 --> 00:04:06.160
Bryce's?

00:04:06.160 --> 00:04:07.160
That's not fair.

00:04:07.160 --> 00:04:08.160
You said you'd go with me.

00:04:08.160 --> 00:04:09.160
Why don't you cancel on him?

00:04:09.160 --> 00:04:10.160
I can't.

00:04:10.160 --> 00:04:12.160
He really wants me to meet his sister who's in from college.

00:04:12.160 --> 00:04:14.160
And if I don't go, then I'll never meet her.

00:04:14.160 --> 00:04:15.160
Sorry.

00:04:15.160 --> 00:04:20.220
That's great, Alex.

00:04:20.220 --> 00:04:21.220
Don't be a brat.

00:04:21.220 --> 00:04:29.100
Let me go.

00:04:29.100 --> 00:04:30.100
Hey.

00:04:30.100 --> 00:04:31.100
Can you believe that?

00:04:31.100 --> 00:04:33.100
First she's late, then she cancels on me.

00:04:33.100 --> 00:04:34.100
I'm sorry, Annie, but you know what?

00:04:34.100 --> 00:04:36.100
I have a little work to finish up and then I can go with you.

00:04:36.100 --> 00:04:37.100
That's okay, Mom.

00:04:37.100 --> 00:04:38.100
Forget it.

00:04:38.100 --> 00:04:40.100
Look, your sister's very busy right now.

00:04:40.100 --> 00:04:42.100
Her life is changing.

00:04:42.100 --> 00:04:44.100
You're just going to have to get used to it, I'm afraid.

00:04:44.100 --> 00:04:46.100
Yeah, but we used to at least do stuff together.

00:04:46.100 --> 00:04:49.100
Now she acts like I'm just in the way or something.

00:04:49.100 --> 00:04:51.100
Oh, that's not true.

00:04:51.100 --> 00:04:53.830
Yes, it is.

00:04:53.830 --> 00:05:08.020
So, what you're telling me is if this substance you've developed comes in contact with GC-161

00:05:08.020 --> 00:05:12.020
or anything containing its properties, it will react strongly?

00:05:12.020 --> 00:05:27.180
Well, let me show you.

00:05:27.180 --> 00:05:29.180
Excellent work.

00:05:29.180 --> 00:05:30.180
Thank you.

00:05:30.180 --> 00:05:35.180
Though I still don't quite understand why you wanted me to develop something like this, Miss Aitron.

00:05:35.180 --> 00:05:41.180
You know, George, I plan to eventually fill you in on all of our long-range plans for GC-161,

00:05:41.180 --> 00:05:44.180
but not yet, so drop it.

00:05:44.180 --> 00:05:50.180
Oh, and I'd like for you to prepare for me a large amount of this sample to say a leader

00:05:50.180 --> 00:05:53.180
and have it delivered to my office first thing in the morning.

00:05:53.180 --> 00:06:02.050
I'm leaving.

00:06:02.050 --> 00:06:04.050
I'll be back by 11.

00:06:04.050 --> 00:06:05.050
Yes, you will.

00:06:05.050 --> 00:06:07.050
Have a great time.

00:06:07.050 --> 00:06:12.050
Oh, I forgot to tell you girls, the plant carnival is the day after tomorrow.

00:06:12.050 --> 00:06:13.050
Oh, cool.

00:06:13.050 --> 00:06:15.050
We can go after school.

00:06:15.050 --> 00:06:18.050
I think I've outgrown the cotton candy and the ferris wheels.

00:06:18.050 --> 00:06:20.050
I mean, we go together every year.

00:06:20.050 --> 00:06:22.050
Not this year, Alex.

00:06:22.050 --> 00:06:25.050
I'm sure you and your friends will have a much better time without me, okay?

00:06:25.050 --> 00:06:33.890
See ya.

00:06:33.890 --> 00:06:35.890
That's amazing.

00:06:35.890 --> 00:06:40.890
Without even realizing it, he's given us the greatest tool yet for finding the kid.

00:06:40.890 --> 00:06:44.890
Considering up till now our best tool is Dave, that's not surprising.

00:06:44.890 --> 00:06:45.890
Thanks, Vince.

00:06:45.890 --> 00:06:52.100
The most obvious place to use this substance is at the plant carnival.

00:06:52.100 --> 00:06:55.100
I love a carnival.

00:06:55.100 --> 00:06:56.100
What did you have in mind?

00:06:56.100 --> 00:06:59.100
I was thinking of taking him out back, getting some honey and ready answers.

00:06:59.100 --> 00:07:01.100
Not Dave, I mean the carnival.

00:07:01.100 --> 00:07:04.100
What is every kid that comes to the carnival need?

00:07:04.100 --> 00:07:06.100
A passion for fun.

00:07:06.100 --> 00:07:07.100
A ticket.

00:07:07.100 --> 00:07:13.100
We code each ticket with this substance, seal the exits, and sit back and wait for the results.

00:07:13.100 --> 00:07:24.630
I love it.

00:07:24.630 --> 00:07:26.630
So tonight is definitely out of the question.

00:07:26.630 --> 00:07:29.630
Bryce, I can't just completely abandon my schoolwork.

00:07:29.630 --> 00:07:32.630
That one knife that off isn't exactly abandonment, Annie.

00:07:32.630 --> 00:07:36.630
I mean, I thought you decided you were going to live in the real world a little more.

00:07:36.630 --> 00:07:38.630
Very funny.

00:07:38.630 --> 00:07:39.630
Oh, what about tomorrow?

00:07:39.630 --> 00:07:41.630
Tomorrow I'm doing this magic show at the plant carnival.

00:07:41.630 --> 00:07:43.630
I do it every year.

00:07:43.630 --> 00:07:44.630
Well, hey, why don't you help me out?

00:07:44.630 --> 00:07:46.630
I can use an assistant.

00:07:46.630 --> 00:07:48.630
You don't exactly strike me as the magic show type.

00:07:48.630 --> 00:07:49.630
Well, no, I mean, it's pretty cool.

00:07:49.630 --> 00:07:52.630
I don't wear a top hat or a sparkly jacket or anything.

00:07:52.630 --> 00:07:54.630
I don't have the first thing about magic, Bryce.

00:07:54.630 --> 00:07:57.630
Somehow I knew that.

00:07:57.630 --> 00:07:58.630
Well, don't worry.

00:07:58.630 --> 00:08:00.630
I mean, I promise you you'll have a great time.

00:08:00.630 --> 00:08:03.630
And if you really hate it, then I promise that I'll join you at one of those

00:08:03.630 --> 00:08:06.630
laugh-a-minute physics seminars that you go to.

00:08:06.630 --> 00:08:09.980
So will you do it?

00:08:09.980 --> 00:08:11.980
I guess it won't kill me.

00:08:11.980 --> 00:08:12.980
Probably not.

00:08:12.980 --> 00:08:17.540
Hey, Alex, you don't say hello?

00:08:17.540 --> 00:08:19.540
Hey.

00:08:19.540 --> 00:08:21.540
Did you know your sister's about to enter a new career?

00:08:21.540 --> 00:08:22.540
Bryce.

00:08:22.540 --> 00:08:23.540
She's working with me at the plant carnival.

00:08:23.540 --> 00:08:25.540
You should come see her in action.

00:08:25.540 --> 00:08:28.540
You're going to the carnival with Bryce, Annie?

00:08:28.540 --> 00:08:30.540
Uh, yeah.

00:08:30.540 --> 00:08:33.540
Just to help him out, to work.

00:08:33.540 --> 00:08:36.540
Well, it's not really work.

00:08:36.540 --> 00:08:37.540
Do me a favor, Annie.

00:08:37.540 --> 00:08:40.540
Just don't talk to me anymore, OK?

00:08:40.540 --> 00:08:42.540
She's so mad.

00:08:42.540 --> 00:08:47.740
I'm not mad.

00:08:47.740 --> 00:08:49.740
You wanted me immediately, Miss Atron?

00:08:49.740 --> 00:08:53.740
Vince, I was just telling Mr. Lawless here how delighted we are

00:08:53.740 --> 00:08:55.740
to have a visitor from the federal government.

00:08:55.740 --> 00:08:57.740
What are you doing here?

00:08:57.740 --> 00:09:00.740
When I fired you, I meant it, Gino.

00:09:00.740 --> 00:09:03.740
That's Inspector Gino Lawless,

00:09:03.740 --> 00:09:06.740
US government special investigator, Vince.

00:09:06.740 --> 00:09:07.740
What?

00:09:07.740 --> 00:09:10.740
Vince, you obviously know this man.

00:09:10.740 --> 00:09:12.740
Yeah, he knows me.

00:09:12.740 --> 00:09:13.740
And you should, too.

00:09:13.740 --> 00:09:16.740
I worked for Vince in his security force.

00:09:16.740 --> 00:09:18.740
Worst job I ever had.

00:09:18.740 --> 00:09:20.740
Every day, he found a new way to humiliate us.

00:09:20.740 --> 00:09:23.740
Oh, you just couldn't take the heat, Gino.

00:09:23.740 --> 00:09:24.740
You're a sick person, Vince.

00:09:24.740 --> 00:09:26.740
I feel sorry for you, I really do.

00:09:26.740 --> 00:09:28.740
But I knew one day I'd get my revenge.

00:09:28.740 --> 00:09:32.740
And here I am, with Uncle Sam backing me up.

00:09:32.740 --> 00:09:34.740
Well, I don't care who you work for.

00:09:34.740 --> 00:09:37.740
You can't just bust in here and make false accusations.

00:09:37.740 --> 00:09:39.740
I remember what goes on here.

00:09:39.740 --> 00:09:43.740
The secret midnight deliveries, the harsh, harsh chemical research.

00:09:43.740 --> 00:09:45.740
You think you're playing with children here?

00:09:45.740 --> 00:09:47.740
You have some imagination, Gino.

00:09:47.740 --> 00:09:51.740
This is the safest, most law-biting chemical plant in the country.

00:09:51.740 --> 00:09:53.740
We'll see about that, Vince.

00:09:53.740 --> 00:09:56.740
I'm going through this place inch by inch.

00:09:56.740 --> 00:09:58.740
And if I find so much as a dirty cup,

00:09:58.740 --> 00:10:03.050
I'll burn you so bad your teeth will melt.

00:10:03.050 --> 00:10:07.050
You'll need an official inspection notice, Wallace.

00:10:07.050 --> 00:10:09.050
Oh, I have one, Vince.

00:10:09.050 --> 00:10:11.050
Here's your 24-hour notice.

00:10:11.050 --> 00:10:13.050
See you in the morning.

00:10:13.050 --> 00:10:19.980
Vince, I need you to hide not only all GC-161,

00:10:19.980 --> 00:10:21.980
but all research pertaining to it.

00:10:21.980 --> 00:10:23.980
If he finds anything, we're sunk.

00:10:23.980 --> 00:10:27.840
I'm on it.

00:10:27.840 --> 00:10:45.480
Yes, ma'am.

00:10:45.480 --> 00:10:47.480
I'm married, too.

00:10:47.480 --> 00:10:49.480
That sounds like you're jealous, Alice.

00:10:49.480 --> 00:10:52.480
Yeah, I thought you said you kind of liked this brice guy.

00:10:52.480 --> 00:10:54.480
I did. I mean, I do.

00:10:54.480 --> 00:10:58.480
Face you. You're just mad because Annie didn't go to the carnival with you this year.

00:10:58.480 --> 00:11:02.480
It's not it. Completely.

00:11:02.480 --> 00:11:04.480
Wouldn't you much rather go with us?

00:11:04.480 --> 00:11:05.480
I mean, we're so much more...

00:11:05.480 --> 00:11:06.480
Annoying?

00:11:06.480 --> 00:11:09.480
That wasn't the word I was looking for.

00:11:09.480 --> 00:11:12.480
Look, Alice, imagine if you had a little sister.

00:11:12.480 --> 00:11:15.480
You wouldn't want her tagging along with us, would you?

00:11:15.480 --> 00:11:33.830
Wow.

00:11:33.830 --> 00:11:35.830
Brice is incredible. Who designed it?

00:11:35.830 --> 00:11:37.830
Well, who do you think?

00:11:37.830 --> 00:11:38.830
You did?

00:11:38.830 --> 00:11:41.830
It's amazing. I never knew you were so creative.

00:11:41.830 --> 00:11:43.830
You never asked.

00:11:43.830 --> 00:11:45.830
So, what are you going to want me to do?

00:11:45.830 --> 00:11:47.830
Wear a top hat and a sparkly jacket,

00:11:47.830 --> 00:11:49.830
and hand me props when I need them.

00:11:49.830 --> 00:11:51.830
Excuse me.

00:11:51.830 --> 00:11:52.830
I'm just kidding.

00:11:52.830 --> 00:11:54.830
I just have to teach you the tricks I'll be doing,

00:11:54.830 --> 00:11:56.830
and you'll help me in setting up the illusion.

00:11:56.830 --> 00:12:00.360
So you're in?

00:12:00.360 --> 00:12:02.360
For you. Maybe.

00:12:02.360 --> 00:12:03.360
Great.

00:12:03.360 --> 00:12:06.360
Now, there's really only five tricks that magicians use

00:12:06.360 --> 00:12:08.360
over and over again in different ways.

00:12:08.360 --> 00:12:10.360
Watch.

00:12:10.360 --> 00:12:12.360
See this hat? It's empty, right?

00:12:12.360 --> 00:12:33.620
I don't know about you guys,

00:12:33.620 --> 00:12:35.620
but our plan is just right.

00:12:35.620 --> 00:12:37.620
Having had a bite to eat all day,

00:12:37.620 --> 00:12:41.620
the body's prepared for a massive influx of junk food.

00:12:41.620 --> 00:12:43.620
Maybe you should think twice, Frank.

00:12:43.620 --> 00:12:45.620
I mean, what is junk food filled with?

00:12:45.620 --> 00:12:46.620
Chemicals.

00:12:46.620 --> 00:12:49.620
We're going to a carnival hosted by a chemical plant.

00:12:49.620 --> 00:12:51.620
Imagine what's in their hot dogs.

00:12:51.620 --> 00:12:54.620
And Nicole, you make chemicals sound like a bad thing.

00:12:54.620 --> 00:12:55.620
Yes.

00:12:55.620 --> 00:12:58.620
Ho, ho, ho! Here you go, kitties.

00:12:58.620 --> 00:13:00.620
This ticket is your pass to all the fun

00:13:00.620 --> 00:13:03.620
that the PVCP carnival has to offer.

00:13:03.620 --> 00:13:05.620
You need to keep the tickets on you at all times.

00:13:05.620 --> 00:13:06.620
Why?

00:13:06.620 --> 00:13:08.620
Cos Miss H.I.N. is going to announce the winner

00:13:08.620 --> 00:13:09.620
of the plant raffle,

00:13:09.620 --> 00:13:11.620
and the number on your ticket is your raffle number.

00:13:11.620 --> 00:13:13.620
Yeah, look, we really have a chance to win.

00:13:13.620 --> 00:13:15.620
The number's going to be picked at random.

00:13:15.620 --> 00:13:16.620
Everybody has a chance.

00:13:16.620 --> 00:13:17.620
Oh, yeah, right.

00:13:17.620 --> 00:13:19.620
How much you want to bet the winner's the kid

00:13:19.620 --> 00:13:20.620
to the plant?

00:13:20.620 --> 00:13:27.970
Hey, are you okay?

00:13:27.970 --> 00:13:28.970
You look really pale.

00:13:28.970 --> 00:13:29.970
Well, to be honest, no.

00:13:29.970 --> 00:13:31.970
I'm starting to feel a little nauseous.

00:13:31.970 --> 00:13:33.970
That veggie burger I had's talking to me,

00:13:33.970 --> 00:13:35.970
and it's not happy.

00:13:35.970 --> 00:13:37.970
Maybe we should just cancel the shop.

00:13:37.970 --> 00:13:38.970
We can't cancel now.

00:13:38.970 --> 00:13:40.970
I don't get donations until the end.

00:13:40.970 --> 00:13:42.970
I'm pretty sure I can make it.

00:13:42.970 --> 00:13:43.970
Pretty sure?

00:13:43.970 --> 00:13:44.970
Well, yeah, and if I can't,

00:13:44.970 --> 00:13:46.970
then you could do the show, eh?

00:13:46.970 --> 00:13:49.970
Ho, no, I can't, right?

00:13:49.970 --> 00:13:50.970
Sure you can.

00:13:50.970 --> 00:13:51.970
You learned everything.

00:13:51.970 --> 00:13:52.970
You know it as well as I do.

00:13:52.970 --> 00:13:55.970
Bryce, I beg you, don't do that to me.

00:13:55.970 --> 00:14:02.030
We thoroughly appreciate the government's concern

00:14:02.030 --> 00:14:04.030
when it comes to safety, Mr. Lawless.

00:14:04.030 --> 00:14:06.030
Lay off the sell job, Ms. Atron.

00:14:06.030 --> 00:14:08.030
I know the only thing you appreciate is your profit margin.

00:14:08.030 --> 00:14:09.030
Why?

00:14:09.030 --> 00:14:11.030
You certainly seem to have a chip on your shoulder

00:14:11.030 --> 00:14:13.030
when it comes to your experience here.

00:14:13.030 --> 00:14:15.030
But I understand that Vince was probably a tough man.

00:14:15.030 --> 00:14:17.030
Vince, Ms. Atron,

00:14:17.030 --> 00:14:19.030
he's not only sadistic and cruel,

00:14:19.030 --> 00:14:20.030
but I have no doubt he's engaged

00:14:20.030 --> 00:14:22.030
in highly illegal and unethical practices

00:14:22.030 --> 00:14:25.030
in the guise of being your security chief.

00:14:25.030 --> 00:14:28.030
Tell me, why would the CEO of a chemical plant

00:14:28.030 --> 00:14:32.030
need such a highly trained XCIA operative to protect her?

00:14:32.030 --> 00:14:35.500
Perhaps we should finish the tour.

00:14:35.500 --> 00:14:49.250
I'm sorry, Annie, I gotta stop.

00:14:49.250 --> 00:14:51.250
No, Bryce, no way, don't do this to me!

00:14:51.250 --> 00:15:02.020
Vince!

00:15:02.020 --> 00:15:04.020
Vince?

00:15:04.020 --> 00:15:06.020
Is it legal to block off the exits

00:15:06.020 --> 00:15:07.020
and not let anybody leave?

00:15:07.020 --> 00:15:09.020
Dave, you worry too much.

00:15:09.020 --> 00:15:11.020
I mean about what's legal, what's not legal.

00:15:11.020 --> 00:15:13.020
Besides, we're not preventing anyone from leaving,

00:15:13.020 --> 00:15:16.020
we're just delaying their departures.

00:15:16.020 --> 00:15:23.880
Want some cotton candy? I can get us some cotton candy.

00:15:23.880 --> 00:15:26.880
Just keep your eyes out, Dave.

00:15:26.880 --> 00:15:29.880
That substance is working like I hope it is.

00:15:29.880 --> 00:15:31.880
There might be some kid out here

00:15:31.880 --> 00:15:34.880
who wishes he or she

00:15:34.880 --> 00:15:40.410
hadn't come out to the carnival today.

00:15:40.410 --> 00:15:43.410
You know what, you guys should really lay off the food a little.

00:15:43.410 --> 00:15:44.410
Come on, Nicole, don't be so boring.

00:15:44.410 --> 00:15:45.410
You know what you wanna bite?

00:15:45.410 --> 00:15:47.410
